==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*amaitjo'' (perhaps ‘biting animal’), from ''*a-'' ‘off’ + ''*mait-'' ‘cut’.  Cognate with Old High German [[ameiza|āmeiza]] (German [[Ameise]]), Middle Dutch [[amete|āmete]].

